events.name: Machine Learning Cloud Study Jam (NLP Track)
events.description:
We are excited to announce the first GDG Cloud KC event! Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with Machine Learning exploring the latest Google Cloud technologies. The event is limited to 20 participants and to attend you will need to RSVP by Wednesday November 13th.

The day will consist of five lab sessions focused on Natural Language Processing and lunch will be provided!

After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Schedule:

9:00am Welcome! (Coffee and Bagels)
9:15am Get free access to Qwiklabs
9:30am Lab 1: Cloud ML Engine: Qwik Start
10:15am Lab 2: Google Cloud Speech API: Qwik Start
11:00am Lab 3: Cloud Natural Language API: Qwik Start

11:45am Lunch Break & Networking
(Lunch will be provided and plans are in process. Let us know if you have suggestion or any specific dietary requirements)

12:30pm Lab 4: Entity and Sentiment Analysis with the Natural Language API
1:15pm Lab 5: Speech to Text Transcription with the Cloud Speech API
2:00pm Wrap up

group_profile.intro: Hi!  I am Josh Durham, a professional software developer and technology enthusiast.  Machine learning is a beautiful intersection of mathematics and computer science and I can't wait to explore this fascinating topic with Kansas City.
